			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 10 Bard Issues compiled<a name="50467"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 7 04 9:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">10) Make songs auto-stop when a new song begins to eliminate double-tapping (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) Twisting problems post-DX9 (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) Increase melee damage mitigation (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) Create hotkeys for instrument-swapping (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) Give us more varied songs in OoW (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) AE songs overwritten by bards with lower cap (2) 
<br />

<br />
10) Make lockpick better/more useful (2) </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
I agree with Visidia, the only one in the tie for 10th place list that is important at all is the bard song stacking. The others are pointless, useless for the most part, or just redundant. Make songs auto-stop when a new song begins, um...macro much? 
<br />

<br />
Eh some of those aren't even issues, bards get lockpicking, I find it usefull for menial stuff like opening chests in LDoN and popping the rock on the way to Ruins of Old Paineel. For the tougher stuff, leave those to a rogue, its the way it was meant to be and rightly so.
<br />

<br />
I should probably voice my opinion in the other thread but since its laid out so clearly here what some of my fellow bards feel need to be fixed, added, or removed I'll reply to this thread.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">2) Weapon procs &amp; casting bar (10)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Ok its annoying, but there are more important issues here than a simple cosmetic error.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">5) Better group invisibility w/ improved duration &amp; range (4)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
To me, this request is low on the priority list if it should be there at all. What level would such a song/ability exist? I'd think at least in the later half of the game, where invis items/spells abound and if not theres cheap 10pp invis potions on NPC vendors. While it is true that bards are built to travel, we are not built to lead. Learn to use what you already have to counter the disadvantages such as have everyone follow the same person the bard is following. Lack of ingenuity is not best resolved through getting tossed a bone from SoE, innovate!
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">4) Instrument modifier caps (5) - Not everybody specified whether they wanted the caps raised or eliminated (and the AAs refunded), but I'd assume the latter.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I know our top 10 list is specifically from the EQdiva community, but if you are at all in doubt or unclear of the issue surrounding mod caps, head over to the issues section of the bard forums at EQlive. Another bard(pardon I forget the name and the EQlive site is being updated at the moment) has written a very comprehensive and extremely clear essay on the topic of why bard mod caps should be removed.
<br />

<br />
For me, the top issue is stacking. Whether its the first in first out style of bard song stacking or stacking usefullness of bards on a raid. At a certain point, having 1 more bard on a raid will incur a diminishing return. Not so with other classes. One more cleric,druid,shaman offers more healing(what raid wouldn't want one more cleric?), more efficient buffing, faster recovery from downtime. More monks/rogues/wizards/necros/magicians/BLs offer more DPS with out any stacking issues(especially now that mob debuff limit is being changed). More enchanters offer more crowd control, more DPS through charmed pets, more efficient buffing. More paladins/SKs/Warriors allow more DPS, more options for OTing without a diminishing return on adding one more such character. 
<br />

<br />
But bards? After your DPS groups are filled(2 or 3 at the most), Your MA group is complete(1), your caster groups are satisfied(another 2 or 3?) adding one more bard gives you nothing but poor DPS, a role better filled by any number of other classes. Heck lets take it to the extreme, even if you have 12 bards in a 72 person raid having one assigned to each group, what use is a 13th bard? Not much. Would you say the same about a 13th monk? a 13th rogue? Would you take a 13th bard over a 13th of ANY other class?
<br />

<br />
That, to me, is the biggest issue for bards. Sure it doesnt affect the lower level folks or the non-high end bards(like me), but the game is about seeing the high end, experience the content, to do so requires raiding(another big issue IMO, but not bard specific), and raiding places a big diminishing return on bards.
<br />

<br />
I honestly don't know how the problem could be resolved. We had a thread discuss giving bards more DPS, Im willing to ask for that. Or perhaps make changes to bard stacking that would make bards valuable as a whole, not just one at a time.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
