				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Info<a name="50518"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 7 04 12:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">10) Make songs auto-stop when a new song begins to eliminate double-tapping (2)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is already in the game.  For your song twists make the following HOTKEYS (where 1, 2, and 3 are the songs you twist):
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 2
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 3
<br />

<br />
Leave the remaining songs as gems in your hotkey bank so you can use them to stop playing any given song, etc.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">3) Song pulses &amp; drops on the same tick (9)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I've watched this happen for years and have come to the conclusion there is nothing anyone can do about it.  It's got to be caused by information between your PC and the game server passing eachother &quot;in the phone line&quot;.  You refreshed your song, the game sees it fade on the server so it sends out the info.  The song refreshes on your PC and <i>then</i> the server info gets to it saying it faded and <b>bam</b> it fades again.
<br />

<br />
No matter what they changed the duration of buffs to this would happen as people would get a little more lazy and twist songs at the last second (or try to cram another song in their twist).. which is exactly what causes it to happen in the first place.
<br />

<br />
Fortunately, you can stop dropped songs from happening entirely by getting a broadband connection, a machine capable of running the game somewhat smoothly and <u>twisting songs the instant you see the previous one refresh</u>.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
