			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 10 Bard Issues compiled<a name="50529"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 7 04 1:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Tremolo, if I remember correctly, the AE songs overwritten thing is as follows -- Level is the sole determinant of whose AE overwrites all other bards. Modifiers like IM/SM/AT are not taken into effect so you could have a 65 bard with no instrument and no AAs overwriting Elemental Chorus from a 64 bard with a Rathe Drum and IIM -- clearly detrimental to the raid. I'm not sure how it breaks ties within level - something you will need to know about. Anyone want to add more info? My guild only has 2 bards so we just don't deal with this issue much.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
A level 64 bard with Jamfest 2 or better would overwrite a level 65 bard without Jamfest.  Jamfest level and bard level are the only things taken into account on bard stacking that I know.  The problem with trying to push for including modifiers (aa/item) into the mix is that it then pushes it outside the realm of just being bardic in nature.  Casters have the same problem with time extension.  A max extended kei buff from a level 65 enchanter doesn't block a non-extended kei buff from a 65 enchanter.  The same is true for time extension items.
<br />

<br />
Two level 65 bards with the same level of jam fast will just continually overwrite each other singing the same song.  Basic song stacking rules apply first, then bard level, with level taking into account Jam Fest level. Therefore, the only real way to handle overwriting is to assign song tasks to the appropriate bard(s), the same way CCH rotations, MT tanking orders, etc., are assigned. A side benefit of it though is that if multiple bards are at the same level and modifier they can both twist the same song.  This will just mean they continually overwrite each other.  Missed notes and stuns wouldn't have a major impact on song droppage for those times when the resists are critical, yet allowing for twisting more than just aoe resists.
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
