				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Fortunately, you can stop dropped songs from happening entirely by getting a broadband connection, a machine capable of running the game somewhat smoothly and twisting songs the instant you see the previous one refresh. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This, while maybe meaning well, isn't accurate, and could be taken as a put down. Yes, these can affect twisting ability, but can missed notes, network latency, and a host of other things.  Even a statement of just let one song run can stop song droppage entirely wouldn't be accurate, as a severe server lag could cause the song to drop, even though it is cycling.
<br />

<br />
As far as the supposed double tap removal item, it shouldn't be there.  Stopsong is the item used to stop songs.  If SOE added this suggestion into the game, it would force every single bard in the game to have a single hotkey for Stopsong, as it would be the only way to totally stop singing
<br />
whatsoever.  Some bards use macros, some don't.  And some use them on some songs but not others.  This suggestion would totally destroy the ability to choose what works best for the individual player, and would be more detrimental to the game than a blessing in my opinion.  Only two people suggested it?  I strongly suggest it be removed. 
