				<td colspan="2"><span>To me, the whole invis thing is a little exagerrated. Guilds place requirements on having an invis item, raiding guilds REQUIRE a fast way to invis. Anyone lvl 65 has no reason NOT to have some way of invising themselves. 
<br />

<br />
Its nice to be able to run people through hostile zones but unless you make your invis song REALLY long range you wont be solving the problem, people will still get lost, go the wrong way, find a way to get dead. In such hostile zones as Qvic or even Barindu a bard is really not suited to escort. People need longer lasting invis for themselves in higher level content. 
<br />

<br />
I can see reasonable arguments for lower lvl content where personal invis is not a high priority. I honestly don't see this as a bard issue, however.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">And NO, I shouldn't have to target and follow the slowest member of the group.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This reminds me of the weakest link. No you don't have to follow the slowest member, but can they follow you? I thought the purpose was to avoid people dying. If you ignore the slowest person then they will eventually fall behind and die. You will either have to slow yourself down or follow the slowest person. Or heck, screw it all, have them die and /consent you <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> . with the new /corpse range change you can drag them at selos speed with no problem.</span></td>
